this tool reads from.

Differences from CAMP
---------------------
- Read-only enforced: all tenant audit-log writes, execution beacons, telemetry
  network calls, and consent prompts present in CAMP have been removed.
- No automatic module installation.
- No remediation scripts that create or modify tenant policies.
- Framework-neutral: findings are NOT mapped to SOC 2, ISO 27001, NIST, CMMC, SSPA,
  or any other compliance framework. Control mapping is left to a separate GRC process.
- No content collection by default (no document/email/prompt content, file names,
  or matched values).

Third-party components used by the HTML report (if/when bundled) retain their own
licenses and are attributed in the report output and/or docs.
